## Database Conventions

Rails uses **convention over configuration** for database design.

### Table Naming

```ruby
# Model name (singular, CamelCase)
Article

# Table name (plural, snake_case)
articles

# Examples:
User          → users
Comment       → comments
ArticleTag    → article_tags
Category      → categories
Person        → people (irregular plural)
```

### Column Naming

```ruby
# Use snake_case for column names
user_id
created_at
published_at
article_title
first_name
email_address

# Avoid:
userId        # camelCase
CreatedAt     # PascalCase
article-id    # kebab-case
```

